The paper deals with the Steiner point removal problem, which is a problem in graph theory and optimization. The problem involves finding a minor of a weighted graph with only a given set of terminals as its vertex set, while preserving the distance between the terminals up to a small multiplicative distortion. This problem is relevant to several areas of computer science, including discrete mathematics (cs.DM), computational geometry (cs.CG), data structures and algorithms (cs.DS), information theory (cs.IT), and social and information networks (cs.SI). Therefore, these are the most likely arXiv CS sub-categories for this paper.
